When the user asks to **update dependencies**, **check for outdated packages**, **bump dependencies**, **run a security audit**, or **open dependency update PRs** in a React Native or Expo app:

1. Read `.cursor/skills/dependency-management-kit/SKILL.md` in the app, or `$HOME/.cache/CursorReactNativeAgents/dependency-management/.cursor/skills/dependency-management-kit/SKILL.md` after cache refresh.
2. Do **NOT** summarize the plan or confirm you read it — execute immediately.
3. Begin **Phase 0** per the strict execution rules in that skill.

Never push to the base branch — every group gets its own branch and PR.
Never bump `react`/`react-native`/`expo-*` independently of the Expo SDK cohort.
Never run `audit fix --force`, `--legacy-peer-deps`, or major bumps outside the gated major-migration phase.
